      "source": [
        "# PySD usage\n",
        "This notebook shows how to run a simple Vensim model with PySD and feed results to `simgon.clusterer`.\n",
        "\n",
        "MDL dosyasının bulunduğu yerde, path'de pycache ve py dosyaları oluşuyor, onları main kodda fonksiyonun altında silmek lazım.\n",
        "\n",
        "import sys'den model_path'e olan 4 satır package yayımlanmadan silinerek commented linelar kullanılmalıdır."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "#from simgon.clusterer import perform_clustering, simulate_from_vensim\n",
        "\n",
        "#model_path = 'path/to/your/model.mdl'\n",
        "\n",
        "import sys\n",
        "sys.path.insert(0, \"/Users/emirsener/Desktop/ts-clustering\")\n",
        "\n",
        "from simgon.clusterer import perform_clustering, simulate_from_vensim\n",
        "\n",
        "import os\n",
        "model_path = os.path.expanduser('~/Desktop/temperature model/temperature model.mdl')\n",
        "\n",
        "parameter_set = {'Initial actual temperature': [i for i in range(15, 25)],\n",
        "                 'Initial measured temperature': [i for i in range(15, 25)],\n",
        "                 'Desired temperature': [i for i in range(15, 25)],\n",
        "                 'Adjustment time': [i for i in range(1, 6)],\n",
        "                 'Measurement delay': [i for i in range(1, 6)]\n",
        "                }\n",
        "\n",
        "output_of_interest = 'Actual Temperature'\n",
        "\n",
        "simulation_results = simulate_from_vensim(model_path, parameter_set, output_of_interest)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},

            "------------------------------\n",
            "Simulation Run 2:\n",
            "('Initial actual temperature=18, Initial measured temperature=18, Desired temperature=18, Adjustment time=1, Measurement delay=2', array([18., 18., 18., ..., 18., 18., 18.], shape=(3201,)))\n",
            "------------------------------\n",
            "Simulation Run 3:\n",
            "('Initial actual temperature=18, Initial measured temperature=18, Desired temperature=18, Adjustment time=1, Measurement delay=3', array([18., 18., 18., ..., 18., 18., 18.], shape=(3201,)))\n",
            "------------------------------\n",
            "Simulation Run 4:\n",
            "('Initial actual temperature=18, Initial measured temperature=18, Desired temperature=18, Adjustment time=1, Measurement delay=4', array([18., 18., 18., ..., 18., 18., 18.], shape=(3201,)))\n",
            "------------------------------\n",
            "Simulation Run 5:\n",
            "('Initial actual temperature=18, Initial measured temperature=18, Desired temperature=18, Adjustment time=1, Measurement delay=5', array([18., 18., 18., ..., 18., 18., 18.], shape=(3201,)))\n",
            "------------------------------\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "for i, res in enumerate(simulation_results[:5]):\n",
        "    print(f\"Simulation Run {i+1}:\")\n",
        "    print(res)\n",
        "    print(\"-\" * 30)"
      ]
    },
